# Prompt

You are my coding partner. I want you to generate the **entire MVP codebase** for a web application called **CMU Activities App**. Follow these instructions carefully.

---

## **üéØ Purpose of the App**

The app is for **CMU students** to easily create, discover, and join casual campus activities (e.g., pickup basketball, study groups, game nights). This is a **lightweight MVP** (minimum viable product) to be built in \~8 weeks.

---

## **üõ†Ô∏è Tech Stack Requirements**

* **Frontend:** Next.js (React) with Tailwind CSS.

* **Backend:** Supabase (Postgres \+ Auth \+ Row-Level Security).

* **Auth:** Supabase Auth configured with email login restricted to `@andrew.cmu.edu`. (Simulate SSO for MVP.)

* **Maps:** Use Mapbox or a simple map component for location pins.

* **Chat:** Per-event chat using Supabase Realtime.

* **Calendar:** Generate `.ics` files for event sync; also include ‚ÄúAdd to Google Calendar‚Äù link.

* **Notifications:** In-app notifications (not push yet).

---

## **üìä Data Models (Minimal)**

**User**

* id (UUID)

* name (string)

* email (string, must be CMU-only)

* avatar\_url (string, optional)

* grad\_year (int, optional)

* interests (array of strings, optional)

* visibility (enum: public, friends-only, private)

* no\_show\_count (int, default 0\)

**Activity**

* id (UUID)

* host\_id (UUID ‚Üí User)

* title (string)

* tags (array of strings)

* description (text)

* location\_name (string)

* location\_lat (float)

* location\_lng (float)

* start\_at (timestamp)

* end\_at (timestamp)

* capacity (int, optional)

* image\_url (string, optional)

* status (enum: active, ended, canceled)

**RSVP**

* id (UUID)

* activity\_id (UUID ‚Üí Activity)

* user\_id (UUID ‚Üí User)

* status (enum: going, waitlist, canceled)

* joined\_at (timestamp)

* checked\_in\_at (timestamp, optional)

**ChatMessage**

* id (UUID)

* activity\_id (UUID)

* user\_id (UUID)

* body (text)

* created\_at (timestamp)

**Report**

* id (UUID)

* target\_type (enum: user, activity)

* target\_id (UUID)

* reporter\_id (UUID)

* reason (string)

* created\_at (timestamp)

* status (enum: open, resolved)

---

## **üì± Core MVP Features**

1. **Authentication & Profiles**

   * CMU-only login with Supabase Auth (email restricted to `@andrew.cmu.edu`).

   * User profile with name, grad year (optional), and tags/interests.

2. **Create/Host Activity**

   * Title, description, tags, location (map picker or text), start/end time, capacity.

   * Save event to Supabase.

3. **Discover Activities**

   * Feed sorted by: ‚ÄúNow‚Äù, ‚ÄúTonight‚Äù, ‚ÄúThis Weekend‚Äù.

   * Filter by tags, time, and open capacity.

   * Map view (pins with titles).

4. **Join & Coordinate**

   * One-tap join ‚Üí creates RSVP entry.

   * Attendee list (avatars).

   * Auto-generate `.ics` link for calendar sync.

   * Simple per-activity group chat (Supabase Realtime).

5. **Safety & Moderation**

   * Report button for events and users.

   * Hide flagged events from feed.

   * Hosts can remove attendees.

---

## **üñ•Ô∏è Required Screens**

1. **Login / Onboarding**

   * Email login (restricted).

   * Basic profile setup.

# **CMU Activities App: Project Blueprint**

## **üéØ Vision & Problem**

* **Problem:** Current student activity ecosystems (large clubs, listservs, or mass GroupMe/Discord channels) are either too broad or too rigid. Students miss out on spontaneous, small-group experiences that align with their availability and interests.

* **Audience:** CMU students who want **flexible, lightweight ways to meet people**‚Äîwhether it‚Äôs pickup basketball, a study jam, or casual gaming.

The app acts as a **decentralized broadcasting system** for student-driven activities, solving the gap between *formal orgs* and *ad-hoc hangouts*.

---

## **üåü Core Experience**

1. **Post** a quick activity (title, time, place, tag).

2. **Discover** activities happening *now* or later.

3. **Join** in one tap, see who‚Äôs coming, and coordinate.

4. **Verify**‚Äîall users must be CMU-affiliated (Andrew ID login).

5. **Connect**‚Äîfriends, notifications, calendar sync, lightweight chat.

---

## **üì± Key Features**

### **1\. Authentication & Profiles**

* **CMU SSO (Shibboleth/SAML or OAuth via AndrewID).**

* **Profiles:**

  * Name, grad year/program (optional).

  * Interests/tags.

  * Pronouns (opt-in).

  * Profile visibility toggles (friends only, public, minimal).

* Safety: CMU-only ecosystem, no external spam.

---

### **2\. Activity Creation**

* **Required:** title, category tag(s), location (map picker \+ preset CMU spots), start/end time.

* **Optional:**

  * Max \# attendees \+ waitlist.

  * RSVP type (auto-confirm, host approval).

  * Contact info (Discord/IG link).

  * Skill level (casual/competitive).

  * Equipment needed.

  * Images/emoji banners.

  * Cost (if applicable, though no ticket sales allowed).

* **Extras:**

  * ‚ÄúRepeat next week‚Äù template.

  * Conflict check with user‚Äôs calendar.

---

### **3\. Discover & Search**

* **Home feed** sorted by ‚ÄúNow‚Äù, ‚ÄúTonight‚Äù, ‚ÄúThis Weekend‚Äù.

* **Filters:** tags (sports, games, study, etc.), time window, friends going, open spots available.

* **Map view** (location clusters) \+ list view.

* **Quick availability search:** ‚ÄúI‚Äôm free 3‚Äì6pm‚Äù ‚Üí show overlapping activities.

---

### **4\. Joining & Coordination**

* **One-tap join/leave** with auto-RSVP confirmation.

* **Attendee list** (avatars \+ friends highlight).

* **Per-event lightweight chat** (auto-expiring after event ends).

* **Check-in option** at event time ‚Üí helps trust/attendance signals.

* **Calendar sync:** Add to GCal/Apple or ICS file.

---

### **5\. Safety & Moderation**

* **CMU-only login**, blocking/reporting users, and reporting events.

* **Host controls:** close sign-ups, kick users, mark no-shows.

* **Admin tools:** flag queue, freeze/delete events, temporary user bans, anti-spam rate limiting.

* **Policies:**

  * No alcohol-focused or off-campus ticketed events.

  * Max \# events posted per user (e.g., 3/day).

  * Events auto-expire once ended.

---

### **6\. Social Layer**

* **Friend system:** add/remove friends, ‚Äúclose friends‚Äù category.

* **Friend activity feed:** highlights events friends are going to.

* **Push/email notifications:**

  * Join confirmations, waitlist updates.

  * Time-based reminders (e.g., ‚ÄúYour event starts in 30 mins‚Äù).

  * Host updates (capacity full, last-minute dropouts).

---

### **7\. Admin & Analytics**

* **Admin console:** user management, event review, reports dashboard.

* **Analytics:** DAU/WAU, posts vs joins, fill rates, show-up proxies (check-ins), report frequency, time-to-first-join.

---

## **üß© MVP Feature Cut (2‚Äì3 Weeks Build)**

* CMU SSO \+ simple profile.

* Create event: title, tags, location, time, capacity.

* Discover feed (list \+ filters \+ map).

* Join/leave \+ attendees list.

* ICS calendar sync.

* Per-event chat.

* Reporting \+ admin hide.

---

## **üöÄ Nice-to-Have / Future Expansions**

* **Smart matching:** recurring availability ‚Üí auto-suggest weekly groups.

* **Skill ratings (opt-in):** e.g., casual vs competitive basketball.

* **Venue integrations:** Skibo courts, UC game rooms.

* **Event photo recap albums.**

* **Import org calendars** (via Google Calendar API instead of scraping).

* **Personal weekly schedule view:** merge class schedule \+ joined events.

---

## **üìä Data Model (Minimal)**

* **User:** id, name, email, avatar, grad\_year, interests\[\], visibility, rep\_score, no\_show\_count.

* **Activity:** id, host\_id, title, tags\[\], description, location{name, lat, lng}, start\_at, end\_at, capacity, status, image\_url.

* **RSVP:** id, activity\_id, user\_id, status{going, waitlist}, joined\_at, checked\_in\_at.

* **ChatMessage:** id, activity\_id, user\_id, body, created\_at.

* **Report:** id, target\_type{user|activity}, target\_id, reporter\_id, reason, created\_at, status.

---

## **üõ†Ô∏è Tech Stack Notes**

* **Frontend:** Next.js (PWA-first) or React Native via Expo.

* **Backend:** Supabase (Postgres, row-level security) or Firebase.

* **Auth:** CMU SSO integration (Shibboleth/SAML).

# **CMU Activities App ‚Äì Idea-a-thon Deliverable**

---

## **1\. Problem & Audience**

### **Problem Statement**

At CMU, students often **miss opportunities for casual, small-scale community activities** because most existing structures are built around **large organizations, rigid events, or fragmented group chats**. This leads to limited spontaneity and a weaker sense of community connection.

**Guiding Question:**  
 How can we empower CMU students to **easily discover, join, and host small, casual activities** that fit their time, place, and interests?

### **Audience**

* **Primary:** CMU undergraduate and graduate students seeking casual, time-flexible social or activity opportunities.

* **Secondary:** Student leaders who want to expand reach beyond their own clubs or group chats.

### **Why It Matters**

* Strengthens campus community through micro-connections.

* Encourages healthier social life by making spontaneous activities easier.

* Reduces barriers for students new to CMU who don‚Äôt yet have established friend groups.

### **Visual (Problem Snapshot)**

Imagine this:

* Student A wants to play spikeball at The Cut but doesn‚Äôt know who else is free.

* Student B is free at the same time but doesn‚Äôt hear about it until afterward.

* Student C is looking for study buddies at Hunt Library but can‚Äôt find a group chat that fits.

‚Üí All three could have met, but the opportunity was lost.  
 The CMU Activities App bridges that gap.

---

## **2\. Core Idea \+ Features**

### **Pitch (2‚Äì3 Sentences)**

The **CMU Activities App** is a lightweight, student-only platform that enables spontaneous community. Students can **post activities in seconds**, discover events based on their schedule and interests, and **join instantly**‚Äîall verified by CMU ID for trust and safety. Think of it as a **‚Äúcampus-wide spontaneous hangout board‚Äù** that replaces the noise of giant group chats.

### **Key Features (MVP Highlighted)**

1. **CMU SSO Login \+ Profiles** ‚úÖ

   * Secure Andrew ID login.

   * Lightweight profiles with name, program, interests.

2. **Activity Creation & Hosting** ‚úÖ

   * Quick event creation (title, time, place, tags).

   * Optional fields: max people, waitlist, skill level, equipment.

3. **Discover & Search** ‚úÖ

   * Feed of upcoming activities (‚ÄúNow, Tonight, This Weekend‚Äù).

   * Filters by tag, time, location, and ‚Äúfriends going.‚Äù

   * Map view for quick scanning.

4. **Join & Coordinate** ‚úÖ

   * One-tap join.

   * Attendee list \+ ephemeral chat per event.

   * Calendar sync with Google/Apple.

5. **Trust & Safety** ‚úÖ

   * CMU-only login.

   * Report/block features.

   * Auto-expiring events and chats.

### **Uniqueness**

Unlike Discords, GroupMes, or listservs, our solution:

* Is **decentralized** (not club-admin controlled).

* Is **time/location-centric** (not just social group‚Äìcentric).

* Focuses on **small-scale, casual activities** rather than large, planned events.

# **Core Use Cases**

* Post a pick-up activity (e.g., spikeball at the Cut, 5v5 at Skibo, study jam, game night).

* Discover/join nearby or time-matched activities.

* Coordinate (chat/DM), track attendees, and sync to calendars.

* Verify CMU affiliation; keep it safe, lightweight, and spam-free.

# **MVP Features (must-have)**

**Auth & Profile**

* CMU SSO login (Shibboleth/SAML or OAuth via AndrewID email).

* Basic profile: name, program/grad year (optional), interests/tags, pronouns (opt-in), visibility toggles.

**Create/Host Activity**

* Title, tags (e.g., ‚ÄúBasketball‚Äù, ‚ÄúBoard Games‚Äù, ‚ÄúStudy‚Äù), short description.

* Location selector (Named CMU spots \+ freeform \+ map pin).

* Start/end time (single or recurring), time zone fixed to ET.

* Capacity (max \#), waitlist toggle, skill level (casual/competitive), equipment needed.

* Calendar sync: ‚ÄúAdd to Google/Apple‚Äù and **ICS** download.

* Image/emoji banner (quick visual).

**Discover & Search**

* Home feed sorted by ‚ÄúNow‚Äù, ‚ÄúTonight‚Äù, ‚ÄúThis weekend‚Äù.  
* Filters: sport/game tag, time window, distance/area, capacity available, friends going.  
* Map view \+ list view.  
* Quick actions: ‚ÄúI‚Äôm free 3‚Äì6pm‚Äù ‚Üí show matching events.

**Joining & Coordination**

* One-tap join & auto-RSVP confirmation.

* Group chat per activity (lightweight, ephemeral).

* Check-in button at start (optional attendance signal).

**Safety & Trust**

* CMU-only access (email/SSO), report user/event, block user.

* Host controls: kick/no-show flag, close sign-ups, duplicate prevention (soft warning).

* Community guidelines page; quick report reasons (spam/harassment).

**Admin/Moderation**

* Flag queue, event freeze/delete, mute user for X days, sketchy events

* Rate limiting (post frequency), anti-spam heuristics.

# **Nice-to-Have (fast follows)**

**Calendar & ‚ÄúGCal Scraper‚Äù**

* Import public CMU calendars (rec center pickup times, org events) via Google Calendar API or ICS feeds (avoid raw scraping).

* Personal ‚ÄúMy Week‚Äù view combining joined \+ classes (optional, via read-only GCal consent).

* Auto-conflict warnings.

**Growth Loops**

* ‚ÄúRepeat this event next week‚Äù template.

# **Data Model (minimal)**

**User**: id, name, email, avatar, grad\_year, interests\[\], visibility, reputation\_kudos{}, no\_show\_count  
 **Activity**: id, host\_id, title, tags\[\], description, location{name, lat, lng}, start\_at, end\_at, capacity, visibility, status, image\_url  
 **RSVP**: id, activity\_id, user\_id, status{going, maybe, waitlist}, joined\_at, checked\_in\_at  
 **ChatMessage**: id, activity\_id, user\_id, body, created\_at  
 **Report**: id, target\_type{user|activity}, target\_id, reporter\_id, reason, notes, created\_at, status

# **Key Screens**

* **Home/Discover** (feed \+ filters \+ map)

* **Create Activity** (wizard; 2‚Äì3 steps)

* **Activity Detail** (join, attendees, map, chat, calendar)

* **My Stuff** (hosting, going, past)

* **Admin Console** (flags, users, events)

# **Notifications**

* Join/approved/waitlist moved

* Time-based reminders

* Host alerts (capacity reached, last-minute leavers)

* Admin actions (content removed)

# **Privacy/Accessibility**

* FERPA-friendly: minimal data, user controls profile visibility.

* Location rounding (e.g., ‚ÄúThe Cut (approx. 50m)‚Äù).

* A11y: semantic UI, large touch targets, color-contrast, screen reader labels.

# **Tech Notes (suggested)**

* **Web \+ iOS/Android**: Next.js/Expo (React Native) or web-first PWA.

* **Backend**: Supabase (Postgres \+ row-level security) or Firebase; or Rails/NestJS.

* **Auth**: SAML/OAuth via CMU SSO; fallback email magic link (CMU-only).

* **Maps**: Mapbox; **ICS** generation server-side.

* **Push**: Expo or web push \+ email via Resend/SES.

* **Moderation**: simple rules \+ admin panel (e.g., Supabase Studio or custom).

# **Policies & Guardrails**

* Posting limits (e.g., ‚â§3 upcoming events/24h).

* Auto-expire past events; archive chats.

* Prohibit ticket sales/scalping; no alcohol-centric events; emergency guidance link.

# **Analytics (founder-level)**

* WAU/DAU, events posted/joined, fill rate (joined/capacity), show-up proxy (check-ins), report rate, time-to-first-join, % ‚ÄúI‚Äôm free now‚Äù conversions.
